---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-ayodhya.html" headerVariant="guide">

<!-- HERO -->

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">
Local Solar Guide · Ayodhya, Uttar Pradesh
</div>

<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">
Rooftop Solar in Ayodhya
</h1>

<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
Ayodhya homeowners are reducing MVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies.
This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started in Ayodhya.
</p>

<a href="index.html"
   class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">
  Check My Solar Savings
</a>

</div>
</section>

<!-- QUICK FACTS -->

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">MVVNL</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Madhyanchal / UPPCL</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- WHY SOLAR IN AYODHYA -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Ayodhya</h2>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Strong Solar Irradiance</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Ayodhya receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day on average — comfortably above
the threshold for financially viable rooftop solar. Long, sunny summers make the economics of
solar particularly strong for Ayodhya households.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Growing City, Rising Electricity Demand</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Ayodhya is experiencing rapid development and infrastructure growth. As electricity demand and
tariffs rise alongside this growth, locking in rooftop solar generation now protects homeowners
from escalating MVVNL bills over the next two decades.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Summer Bills & Solar Output Align</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
The hottest months drive the highest electricity bills — and are when solar panels generate the
most power. For Ayodhya homeowners, solar output peaks precisely when the financial benefit
of avoiding grid electricity is greatest.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Opportunity</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Ayodhya homeowners with an MVVNL electricity connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar
Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy. MVVNL maintains an empanelled installer list and the
pmsuryaghar.gov.in portal handles all Ayodhya applications.
</p>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- MVVNL NET METERING PROCESS -->

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">MVVNL Net Metering in Ayodhya</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Ayodhya homeowners under MVVNL.</p>

<div class="space-y-4">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via MVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be empanelled with MVVNL under the PM Surya Ghar scheme.
Verify empanelment status on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to MVVNL</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to MVVNL
with technical details of the system. Most empanelled installers handle this on your behalf.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">MVVNL Technical Inspection</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">An MVVNL engineer inspects the installation to verify grid safety compliance.
This typically takes two to four weeks depending on MVVNL workload in Ayodhya.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing MVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter that measures both electricity
imported from and exported to the grid. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once the meter is installed, MVVNL commissions your system. Surplus solar exported
to the grid earns credits on your monthly MVVNL electricity bill from this point forward.</p>
</div>
</div>

</div>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">
See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a>
for a full explanation of how credits appear on your bill.
</p>

</div>
</section>

<!-- SYSTEM SIZES FOR AYODHYA -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Ayodhya</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly MVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>

<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50">
<tr>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly MVVNL Bill</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area Needed</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹800 – ₹2,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="1kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">1kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">80–120 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Small homes, limited roof</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹1,500 – ₹3,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK</td>
</tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50">
<td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td>
<td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC use</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">
Sizes are indicative. Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a>
for the full methodology.
</p>

</div>
</section>

<!-- PM SURYA GHAR -->

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Ayodhya</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
Ayodhya homeowners with an MVVNL connection can apply for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana
central subsidy through the official portal.
</p>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as an Ayodhya Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your MVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select an MVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's installer list</li>
<li>3. Get the system installed, net metering connected, and MVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete the subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited directly to your bank account — typically weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Subsidy amounts are subject to government policy. Always verify current rates at pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">
Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →
</a>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<!-- NEIGHBOURHOODS -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ayodhya Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
We help homeowners across Ayodhya district understand solar options and connect with
MVVNL-empanelled installers in their area.
</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{[
  "Civil Lines", "Faizabad", "Rekabganj", "Sahadatganj", "Naya Ghat",
  "Sugar Mill Colony", "Tulsi Nagar", "Surajkund", "Bihariji", "Kursela",
  "Ram Janmbhoomi Path", "Milkipur", "Sohawal", "Maya Bazar", "Birsinghpur", "Rudauli"
].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>

</div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Ayodhya Solar</h2>

<div class="space-y-4">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Ayodhya?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Ayodhya falls under <strong>MVVNL (Madhyanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary. All net metering applications, bi-directional meter installations, and solar scheme empanelment for Ayodhya homeowners are processed through MVVNL.</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with MVVNL in Ayodhya?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by an MVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to MVVNL. MVVNL inspects the system and replaces your meter with a bi-directional net meter. The process typically takes two to six weeks.</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Ayodhya?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Ayodhya homeowners with an MVVNL connection are eligible. Use an MVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current subsidy amounts and eligibility before applying.</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Ayodhya homes?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For typical Ayodhya homes with monthly MVVNL bills of ₹1,500–₹4,000, a 2kW to 3kW system covers a significant portion of electricity needs. Homes with AC use through summer often benefit from a 3kW system.</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Ayodhya?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost typically ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After the PM Surya Ghar central subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Get quotes from at least two MVVNL-empanelled installers.</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is Ayodhya a good location for solar?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Ayodhya receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day — well suited for rooftop solar. Hot summers mean high solar generation coincides with peak demand, making solar financially effective for most homeowners.</p>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- NEARBY CITIES -->

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
